item.title: Miss add a quote by Harper Lee
item.description: "Until I feared I would lose it, I never loved to read. One does not love breathing." -- Harper Lee

item.title: Miss add a quote by Harper Lee
item.description: "I think there's just one kind of folks. Folks." -- Harper Lee

item.title: Miss add a quote by Donald Miller
item.description: "It occurs to me it is not so much the aim of the devil to lure me with evil as it is to preoccupy me with the meaningless. " -- Donald Miller

item.title: Miss add a quote by Elie Wiesel
item.description: "There is divine beauty in learning... To learn means to accept the postulate that life did not begin at my birth. Others have been here before me, and I walk in their footsteps. The books I have read were composed by generations of fathers and sons, mothers and daughters, teachers and disciples. I am the sum total of their experiences, their quests. And so are you." -- Elie Wiesel

item.title: Miss add a quote by Mark Twain
item.description: "If you tell the truth, you don't have to remember anything." -- Mark Twain
